post_text: Congratulations SRO!
shared_text:
Wakefield Police Department
October 24, 2019 at 3:47 PM ·

Congratulations to Officer Michael Pietrantonio for being selected as our “Officer of the Quarter.” Officer Pietrantonio is a Veteran of the United States Air Force and began with the Wakefield Police Department in 2008. He continued several years of active duty which included a deployment to Iraq during “Operation Iraqi Freedom.” He has been assigned as a School Resource Officer to Northeast Metro Tech since 2012. He has investigated several challenging cases and is always extremely thorough in his work. Officer Pietrantonio is always available to anyone in need of assistance and we appreciate all of his efforts.

He continued several years of active duty which included a deployment to Iraq during “Operation Iraqi Freedom.” He has been assigned as a School Resource Officer to Northeast Metro Tech since 2012. Officer Pietrantonio is always available to anyone in need of assistance and we appreciate all of his efforts.

March 20, 2019 at 12:57 PM ·

A big thank you to the Northeast Metro Tech Carpentry students as well as teacher Richard McGinnis for the new pamphlet rack in the police station lobby.

post_text:
Dear Community,
Every year, during graduation, I make a point of acknowledging any students who are entering military service. It was brought to my attention that during my remarks at this year's ceremonies while recognizing our students who were going to military schools or enlisting, while I mentioned all of the students' names and where they were going. I forgot to mention that two of the students that were joining the United States Marine Corps. I read their names and they stood, but I lost my place and left out their branch of service.

Our students deserve praise for making this choice and I have always felt strongly about recognizing them at our graduation each year.

I sincerely apologize to our two students and their families for this oversight, and I wish them all the best as they move on to their career in the Marine Corps.

Sincerely,
Carla Scuzzarella
